      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening validated against coupon-level titanium alloy test data; contact formulation verified against known analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "Elastic-plastic model with isotropic hardening (Ramberg-Osgood fit) calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V coupon tensile data (N=6 specimens). Augmented Lagrange contact formulation verified against Hertz contact benchmarks. Model form appropriate for quasi-static large-deformation bending of metallic implants. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing; geometric inputs from calibrated CMM measurements of test specimens; coefficient of friction from dedicated tribology characterization.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E = 114 GPa, σ_y = 880 MPa) from lot-specific tensile testing of implant material. Geometry from CMM measurements of each of the 11 test constructs. Friction coefficient (μ = 0.15) from pin-on-disk tribology testing under saline lubrication. Input uncertainty quantified and propagated. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 production-representative constructs tested across two independent laboratories; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawings.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-lot components. Six constructs tested at FDA CDRH laboratory; five at an independent ISO 17025-accredited contract laboratory. CMM inspection confirmed all critical dimensions within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Sample size supports statistical comparison per ASTM E2935. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two distinct loading rates and environmental conditions to characterize condition sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "All testing conducted at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. No variation in loading rate or temperature was explored. This represents a known limitation acknowledged in the assessment: achieved Gradation 2 falls below the required Gradation 3. The shortfall is accepted given that pedicle screw compression-bending is a quasi-static failure mode and rate sensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V at physiological strain rates is negligible per published literature."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/equivalency-of-input-parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
